A man in Kericho has massacred his wife, his kid,3, and eight-year-old nephew. Kericho Police commander James Mogera, the incident happened on Friday at  Kebeneti village, in Soin Sigowet sub-county. Mugera said the man locked up the family in his house before slashing them to death using a panga.. The killer later came out of the house brandishing the panga, to scare away those who had come to rescue the deceased. He was later arrested near Cheptenye Boys High school, some 10 kilometres away. He is being held at Kericho police station and will be arraigned on Monday. The bodies were taken to Sigowet Sub-county Hospital mortuary. Read; Nyandarua man slits his throat after killing niece, attacking mother Click here for the latest political news